HEADWORD: Burghbrech
<hw>Burgh"brech`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Burgh</ets> + F. <ets>br⟦egrave⟧che</ets>, equiv. to E.
<ets>breach</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(AS. Law)</fld> <def>The offense of
violating the pledge given by every inhabitant of a tithing to keep the
peace; breach of the peace.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
